    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_10",
      "description": "Available now is a museum-quality 1995 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the highly sought-after 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged rotary engine. This example maintains factory-spec compression and exhibits no thermal degradation of the complex vacuum system. The chassis integrity is absolute, retaining the original aluminum double-wishbone suspension components and a perfectly balanced 50/50 weight distribution. The five-speed manual transmission shifts with crisp, short-throw engagement, paired with a factory Torsen limited-slip differential for optimal power delivery. The exterior retains its original finish with no evidence of oxidation or panel misalignment, while the interior plastics and leather remain supple and free of UV damage. A rare, unmodified specimen that represents the pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering, fully documented and mechanically synchronized.",
